The paper discusses recommender systems, which are commonly used in information retrieval (cs.IR) and social networks (cs.SOC). The use of network representation in recommendation algorithms also suggests a connection to machine learning (cs.LG) and deep learning (cs.DL). Additionally, the paper discusses the possible influence of recommendation on the evolution of systems, which could be related to social informatics (cs.SI).
